definition.value: A cult with a primary interest in political action and ideology.
A cult with a primary interest in any of various aspects of sexual behavior that are considered socially deviant or otherwise nonnormative.
A cult involved in sex trafficking or that practices any of various forms of sex trafficking.

A cult that teaches and practices polygamy, marriage between more than two people, most often polygyny, one man having multiple wives, have long been noted, although they are a minority. Often, polygamist cults are viewed negatively by both legal authorities and society, and this view sometimes includes negative perceptions of related mainstream denominations, because of their perceived links to possible domestic violence and child abuse.
A cult which practices any of various forms of sexual abuse.
A cult involved in sexual salvery or that practices any of various forms of sexual slavery.
A cult which practices pedophilia or other forms of child sexual abuse; a cult whose members are pedophiles.

A cult which practices prostitution for some purpose, often to bring others into the cult. Such prostitution may be voluntary, involuntary, or fall somewhere inbetween depending on practices of brainwashing within the cult.
A cult which practices incest or whose members engage in incestuous activity (voluntarily, involuntarily, or somewhere inbetween if brainwashing is involved).
Sexual contact which is unreciprocated. A form of sexual harassment and also of sexual assault. This includes a perpetrator forcing a victim to engage in sexual contact.

A paraphilic interest in rubbing, usually one's pelvic area or erect penis, against a non-consenting person for sexual pleasure. It may involve touching any part of the body, including the genital area.

Sexual arousal based on grabbing or rubbing one's hands against an unexpecting (and non-consenting) person. It usually involves touching breasts, buttocks or genital areas, often while quickly walking across the victim's path.
Some psychologists consider toucherism a manifestation of frotteurism, while others distinguish the two.
Fetishistic sexual attraction to obese persons.
A form of fat fetishism in which sexual gratification is obtained not from the fat itself but from the process of gaining, or helping others gain, body fat.

label.value: person who has witnessed a crime

definition.value: A person who perceived any aspect of a crime; typically, a person who saw a crime.

label.value: person who has witnessed a sex crime

definition.value: A person who perceived any aspect of a sex crime; typically, a person who saw a sex crime.

Under U.S. law, a person who first hears an allegation of abuse made by a child or another victim of abuse or sexual crime. The witness is legally obligated to report the abuse, and may be called upon during the trial proceedings.
Pregnancy in human adolescent females under the age of 19.
Pregnancy before a person has reached 13 years of age.
Pregnancy, usually accidental, that is not desired by the parent or parents.
Unintended or accidental pregnancy, including pregnancy resulting from failed contraceptive measures.
The condition of carrying two or more fetuses simultaneously.
The first pregnancy experienced by an animal.
Intended pregnancy, one which is consciously desired at the time of conception or sooner.
Any pregnancy after an animal's first pregnancy.
The condition of carrying twins simultaneously.
The condition of carrying triplets simultaneously.
The condition of carrying quintuplets simultaneously.
The condition of carrying quadruplets simultaneously.
The condition of carrying sextuplets simultaneously.
The condition of carrying septuplets simultaneously.
Pornography which features performers of specific ethnic groups, or depictions of interracial sexual activity.
A form of sexual fetishism involving images of people swimming or posing underwater, and sexual activity in or under water.

A paraphilia in which a person is sexually aroused by the risk of being killed. The fetish may overlap with some other fetishes that risk one's life, such as those involving drowning or choking. This does not necessarily mean the person must actually be in a life-threatening situation, for many are aroused from dreams and fantasies of such.
Any of various sexual fetishes involving balloons.
A paraphilia whereby sexual arousal is obtained from being robbed.
A form of unconventional sexual attraction in which one is aroused by tears or sobbing.
A sexual fetish in which an individual is attracted to dolls and doll like objects such as figurines.
Sexual harassment in which a person is offended by auditory or visual conduct which is offensive to them, but is not directly aimed at them (such as overhearing a sexist joke).
Sexual harassment directly involving a person; sexual harassment directed at a specific person or persons.

A sexual practice involving the application of electrical stimulation to the nerves of the body, with particular emphasis on the genitals, using a power source (such as a TENS, EMS, Violet wand, or made-for-play units) for purposes of sexual stimulation.
Sexual play or erotic situations involving food as a primary component.
Sexual fetishism in which participants are aroused by erotic situations involving food.
A form of sexual fetishism whereby a person becomes aroused when copious amounts of a substance are applied to the naked skin, face, or to clothing.

A paraphilia characterized by the erotic desire to be consumed by, or sometimes to personally consume, another person or creature, or an erotic attraction to the process of eating in general practice.

A paraphilia in which sexual arousal, facilitation, and attainment of orgasm are responsive to and contingent upon being with a partner known to have committed an outrage, cheating, lying, known infidelities, or crime—such as rape, murder, or armed robbery.

Sexual play in which lotion is used specifically as a lubricating medium. Typically lotion play involves a participant rubbing lotion on another using their body, sexual intercourse in a pool or bath filled with lotion, or lotion being poured over the participants during sex.
A model who models fetish clothing or devices that augment their body in a fetish-like manner or in fetishistic situations, though they may not work exclusively in that form of modeling.
Any practice of physically revering a part of another person's body; typically in a sexual context (such as in BDSM).
A form of body worship in which one participant, the worshiper, touches the muscles of another participant, the dominant, in a sexually arousing manner.
